<div class="container">
    <h1>Introduction to Web Communication</h1>
    <p>Web communication is the process by which clients (like browsers or apps) interact with servers over the internet. Understanding this process is fundamental for developing web applications, APIs, and modern online services.</p>

    <h2>Key Concepts</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Client:</strong> The application or device that requests data or services from a server.</li>
        <li><strong>Server:</strong> The system that processes client requests and sends back responses.</li>
        <li><strong>Browser:</strong> The interface used by clients to interact with web applications.</li>
        <li><strong>HTTP Protocol:</strong> The standard way clients and servers communicate over the web.</li>
        <li><strong>Client-Side vs Server-Side:</strong> Operations can occur either in the client’s browser or on the server.</li>
        <li><strong>APIs:</strong> Interfaces that allow applications to exchange data.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>This introduction will prepare you for the next topics, where we will explore the client, server, browser, HTTP, client-side, server-side, and APIs in detail.</p>

